author: Inside Edition
description: ABC is expecting huge ratings with Jimmy Kimmel's return to late night, but two of the biggest station groups, Nexstar and Sinclair, are refusing to air the show. Between them, they control 70 ABC affiliates, which leaves 164 stations that will be airing Kimmel Tuesday night. The production crew at Kimmel's studio got back to work, the live audience arrived, and many are wondering: What will Kimmel say? Will he apologize?
title: What Will Jimmy Kimmel Say During His First Show After Suspension?

author: Inside Edition
description: At age 16, Courtney Stodden's marriage to a 51-year-old actor sent shockwaves across the country. Now, at age 31, Stodden says she was a child bride. Doug Hutchinson was best known for his roles on the TV drama "Lost" and the movie "The Green Mile." However, it was his marriage to Stodden that captured the national spotlight. Hutchinson calls Stodden's claims "false, malicious and egregious." Her story is now depicted in the new Lifetime movie "I Was A Child Bride: The Courtney Stodden Story."
title: Courtney Stodden Says She Was Groomed To Be A Child Bride

author: Inside Edition
description: Police in Seattle say they tried to pull over a vehicle, which they say had a stolen license plate, but the driver wouldn't stop. The chase led through some residential streets, but then came to a drawbridge. While it seemed the suspect was trapped since the bridge was open and traffic wasn't crossing, this daredevil made a break for it anyway. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Suspect Escapes After Driving Over Open Drawbridge To Flee Police In Seattle
